# shadcn/ui is the GodMode design system

All GodMode **user-facing UI** uses the existing shadcn/ui setup in `apps/web` — not one-off CSS, ad-hoc HTML themes, or parallel design systems.

## Source of truth

- App: `apps/web` (Vite + Tailwind v4 + shadcn **base-nova**, icons **lucide**)
- Components: `@/components/ui/*` via `npx shadcn@latest` (run with `-c apps/web` from repo root)
- Tokens: semantic classes (`bg-background`, `text-muted-foreground`, `bg-primary`, …) from `apps/web/src/index.css`
- Follow the Cursor **shadcn** skill and its Critical Rules (forms, composition, styling, icons)

## Required

- Prefer installed shadcn components before custom markup (`Button`, `Card`, `Field`, `Tabs`, `Alert`, `Empty`, `Separator`, `Badge`, `sonner`, …)
- Compose pages from those primitives; do not invent a second visual language
- Use `cn()` for conditional classes; `gap-*` not `space-y-*`; `size-*` for equal dimensions
- Icons: `lucide-react` with `data-icon` on buttons; no manual icon sizing inside shadcn components
- New components: `npx shadcn@latest add … -c apps/web` (or search registries first) — do not paste unrelated UI kits

## Forbidden

- Standalone marketing/landing pages with custom CSS themes that ignore shadcn tokens (e.g. hand-rolled `sites/www/styles.css` look) — build them in `apps/web` (or a Vite app that shares the same shadcn config/tokens)
- Raw color utilities for brand UI (`bg-blue-500`, one-off hex palettes) when a semantic token exists
- Parallel component libraries (MUI, Chakra, raw Bootstrap, etc.) in GodMode surfaces

## Exceptions

- **Bridge / scripts / docs markdown** — not UI
- **Canvas** (`.canvas.tsx`) — Cursor canvas SDK only; not shadcn
- **Third-party plugin web bundles** — may ship their own UI, but Official product chrome stays shadcn

When creating or redesigning any GodMode surface (app, auth, admin, marketing, settings), start from shadcn — do not invent a separate brand stylesheet.
